Paper: hep-th/0207268

Date: 2002-07-30

Title: Fermion mixing in quasi-free states

Authors: K.C. Hannabuss, D.C. Latimer (Oxford)

Comments: 10 pages, Plain TeX

Journal-ref: J.Phys. A36 (2003) L69

Quantum field theoretic treatments of fermion oscillations are typicallyrestricted to calculations in Fock space. In this letter we extend theoscillation formulae to include more general quasi-free states, and alsoconsider the case when the mixing is not unitary.